  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) achieved level equals required level with honestly documented wide uncertainty bounds arising from single-condition testing. Confidence in that factor is explicitly low and fully rationalized; the shortfall is accepted as residual risk with a documented offset rationale. No weakeners should fire on this package.",
