        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 standard test configuration applied consistently across both laboratories. Single test condition (standard F1717 geometry, room temperature, displacement-controlled at 1 mm/min). Gradation 2 requires documented test protocol with controlled and recorded conditions. NOTE: Only one test condition is exercised; confidence in condition-space coverage is explicitly low and documented as a limitation. The wide uncertainty bounds on inter-laboratory variability (CV=8.3% on yield force) are honestly reported and propagated into uval. This limitation is accepted as residual risk given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard for this device class and no additional conditions are required by the applicable guidance."
      },
      "rationale": "Test conditions controlled per ASTM F1717-21: standard L1/L2 geometry, room temperature (23±2°C), displacement-controlled loading at 1 mm/min, load cell calibration NIST-traceable. Protocol identical across both laboratories (verified by inter-laboratory protocol comparison). EXPLICITLY LOW CONFIDENCE NOTE: Only a single test condition (standard F1717 configuration) was exercised. The influence of temperature variation, loading rate sensitivity, and alternate fixation configurations on model predictive accuracy is not bounded by this validation dataset. Inter-laboratory yield-force CV of 8.3% is wider than the 5% target, contributing to elevated uval. These limitations are fully documented and propagated into the validation uncertainty budget rather than suppressed. Achieves Gradation 2 (documented protocol with controlled conditions); does not achieve Gradation 3 (multiple conditions) due to the single-condition constraint."
    },
