  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": "{\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted-2026\", \"type\": \"DecisionRecord\", \"actor\": \"https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel\", \"role\": \"Credibility assessment team\", \"outcome\": \"Accepted\", \"decidedAt\": \"2026-04-19T00:00:00Z\", \"rationale\": \"The FEA ensemble is accepted as credible for predicting ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; 12 of 13 achieve their required gradation level without qualification. The Test conditions factor achieves its required Gradation 2 level but carries explicitly documented low confidence due to single-condition testing and an inter-laboratory yield-force CV of 8.3% that is wider than the 5% target. These limitations are honestly reported and fully propagated into the validation uncertainty budget (uval). Despite the elevated uncertainty, all 33 construct-QoI E/uval values remain below the 1.96 acceptance threshold and all percent differences remain below 10%. The decision to accept is supported by: (1) the single ASTM F1717 test condition being the applicable regulatory standard for this device class, with no additional conditions required by FDA guidance; (2) the wide uncertainty bounds being conservative (they increase uval, making the acceptance threshold harder to satisfy, not easier); and (3) the model risk level of 3 being consistent with a Medium assurance level where residual uncertainty in condition coverage is acceptable given the corroborating bench evidence. The offset rationale for the Test conditions confidence gap is documented in hasOffsetRationale.\", \"hasOffsetRationale\": {\"id\": \"https://uofa.net/nagaraja/offset/test-conditions-single-condition\", \"type\": \"OffsetRationale\", \"name\": \"Offset rationale: Test conditions single-condition coverage and elevated inter-laboratory CV\", \"description\": \"The Test conditions factor achieves Gradation 2 (documented, controlled protocol) but not Gradation 3 (multiple conditions). Confidence is explicitly low: only the standard ASTM F1717 room-temperature, 1 mm/min displacement-controlled configuration was tested, and inter-laboratory yield-force CV of 8.3% exceeds the 5% target. This gap is accepted for the following reasons: (a) ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard configuration as the regulatory acceptance criterion for pedicle screw constructs; FDA guidance does not require multi-condition validation for this device class at this risk level; (b) the wide inter-laboratory CV is conservatively propagated into uval, making the E/uval acceptance criterion more stringent rather than masking the uncertainty; (c) the remaining 12 factors all meet or exceed their required gradation levels, providing a strong overall credibility foundation; and (d) the model risk level 3 / Medium assurance level framework explicitly permits residual uncertainty in condition coverage when the primary regulatory test scenario is fully validated. The gap is documented as a scope limitation for future work: temperature sensitivity and loading-rate studies are recommended prior to any COU expansion beyond standard F1717 conditions.\"}}}",
